transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yes, I wonder if I could upgrade my prescription.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can help you with that. What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 2: It's Pacelli with a P, and the zip code is 14468.

Speaker 1: Okay, I pulled you up here.

Speaker 2: So, when you mean upgrade, do you want to go to the AGV Viagra?

Speaker 1: Yes, I do.

Speaker 2: Got it. So, since you've been a long-term customer of us, you can get it at the promotional rates.

Speaker 1: It's $40 at $163, $25 at $113, and our smallest package is $10 for $63.

Speaker 2: How many do I get per month now?

Speaker 1: Well, right now you're getting 8 per month, and right now the AGV is on a promotional rate.

Speaker 2: Okay, can you give me, what were the options again? Could you run that by me?

Speaker 1: Yeah, of course. 10 pills for $63, 25 pills for $113, and 40 pills for $163.

Speaker 2: Okay, can I get 25?

Speaker 1: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 2: Okay, and that's per month. That's per month, correct?

Speaker 1: The 25 count is going to be a little bit longer. It'll be like 5 to 6 weeks.

Speaker 2: The 10 count is the one that they do per month, but it's usually the better deal. We go for 25.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, that's fine.

Speaker 2: Perfect. And it's going to 125 Curtis Road, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes, correct.

Speaker 2: Alrighty. And just to confirm, the Discover card that ends in 9590, is that okay for the order?

Speaker 1: Yes, that's correct.

Speaker 2: Perfect. One second.

Speaker 1: Alright, you're all set, sir. The order has been placed. Actually, give me one moment. I don't know why this was added to the order.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to have to put you on a brief hold. I have to modify something on your account just to make sure it gets done correctly.

Speaker 1: Okay.
